Removed defmt dependency because:
- we are not using it anymore in `no_std`;
- it was causing problems with `keformatter` (@p-avital).

**In this PR:**
- fixed problem with `default-features` in workspace `Cargo.toml`;
- `zenoh-protocol` and `zenoh-codec` are made competely `no_std`:
  - `zenoh-result` was split from `zenoh-core` (`zenoh-result` supports `no_std`, while `zenoh-core` depends on stuff in `std`);
  - own `IError` in place of `std::core::Error` (until `core::error::Error` is made stable, see its [tracking issue](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/103765)) $-$ the `derive_tryfrom` macro was returning `uhlc::SizeError`s, which are now converted into a new struct `zenoh_protocol::SizeError` in order to implement `zenoh_result::IError`;
  - `AtomicZInt` (`= AtomicU64`) is not portable to `no_std` target, hence it has been moved out of `zenoh_protocol` to the only place in which it is used (namely `zenoh::session`).

The aim of this PR is to move stuff in common/duplicated between crates (mainly dependencies) to the workspace's `Cargo.toml` file, in order to simplify the process of a new Zenoh release.

**What is included in this PR:**
- package metadata that is common to all (or at least most of) the crates was moved to the workspace level, and crates do inherit such properties. Some exceptions to this behavior include:
	- `package.name`/`package.readme`, which are different for every crate;
	- `package.description`/`package.authors`, whose most common values have been moved to the workspace's `Cargo.toml`, but some crates still override those values;
- all dependencies' versions are listed in the workspace's `Cargo.toml` file $-$ each crate, for those dependencies that it needs, inherits the default version from the workspace;
- some dependencies presented some version mismatches $-$ the most recent version among the used ones has been selected;
- some dependencies are always used with some specific features (e.g. feature `derive` on `serde`, or feature `alloc` on `defmt`) $-$ such features have been moved to the workspace's `Cargo.toml` for simplicity;
- crates that need specific features can specify those in addition to the one inherited from the workspace (usual _additivity_ still applies);
- according to [this](https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/2906-cargo-workspace-deduplicate.html#no-longer-need-both-version-and-path-to-publish-to-cratesio) and [this](https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/2906-cargo-workspace-deduplicate.html#path-dependencies-infer-version-directive), `version` directives have been removed from intra-workspace dependencies $-$ **double check behavior on next release**.

Main changes:
- `zenoh-collections` and `zenoh-buffers` tested and working on STM32F7 board (minor fixes);
- in `zenoh-collections`/`zenoh-buffers` added `defmt` feature (opt-in) useful for debugging in `no_std`;
- [WIP] `zenoh-protocol` should be also ok in `no_std`, apart from the few dependencies that it still has in `zenoh-core`. `zenoh-codec` depends on `zenoh-protocol`;
- [WIP] `uhlc` dependency now relies on the GitHub version instead of the `crates.io` one, in order to have `no_std` support;
- ~[WIP] `defmt` feature for `zenoh-protocol`/`zenoh-codec` is almost done, but needs a couple of additions dependent on `defmt` feature in `uhlc` ([PR waiting](https://github.com/atolab/uhlc-rs/pull/6))~ `defmt::Format` is implemented also for structures in `zenoh-protocol`/`zenoh-codec`.
